(Phoenix, AZ) -- Holocaust survivors around the globe are up in arms over a report that Arizona is looking to use &#34;Nazi gas&#34; in executions.
 &#34;The Guardian&#34; reports Arizona prison leaders have already tested out a gas chamber and bought chemicals to make hydrogen cyanide, the same gas Nazis used to kill millions of Jews.
 The International Auschwitz Committee is calling the plan &#34;a disgraceful act that is unworthy of any democracy.&#34;
